-   Accessibility Statement: In the UK, websites are expected to be accessible to all users, including those with disabilities. An accessibility statement communicates your commitment to accessibility and provides information on how users can access your content if they encounter accessibility barriers.

-   Refund Policy (if applicable): If you sell products or services online, a refund policy outlines the terms and conditions under which customers can request refunds for their purchases.

---

DONE: Copyright Notice: This notice informs visitors that the content on your website is protected by copyright law. It specifies who owns the copyright and how users can seek permission to use or reproduce the content.
DONE: Cookie Policy: This page explains how your website uses cookies and similar tracking technologies. It should detail what types of cookies are used, their purposes, and how users can manage or disable them.
DONE: GDPR Compliance Statement: If you collect personal data from individuals in the European Union, including the UK, you need to comply with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). A GDPR compliance statement outlines how your website complies with GDPR requirements for data protection and user privacy.
DONE: Terms of Service (or User Agreement): While similar to terms and conditions, the terms of service specifically govern the use of your website or service by users. It outlines the rules, responsibilities, and expectations for users accessing your site.
DONE: Privacy Policy: This is a legal document that discloses how your business collects, uses, shares, and protects the personal information of visitors and users. It's essential to have a privacy policy, especially if you collect any form of personal data.
DONE: Disclaimer: A disclaimer can limit your liability for the information presented on your website. It typically states that the information provided is for general informational purposes only and should not be construed as professional advice.
